'''replevin'''

(''law'') a personal action which lies <!--correct???--> to recover possession of goods and [[chattel]]s wrongfully taken or detained, or the [[writ]] by which goods and chattels are replevied; <!--this could do with being wikified, but what is the verb?  replevy?  replevie? --> originally, a remedy peculiar to cases for wrongful distress, but now able to be brought in all cases of wrongful taking or [[detention]].